article.headline: Massachusetts 79, La Salle 71
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Stephane Lasme had 17 points, 13 rebounds and nine blocked shots to lead Massachusetts to a 79-71 victory over La Salle on Saturday. Rashaun Freeman added 18 points and 11 rebounds, and James Life had 16 points for the Minutemen (11-4, 1-0 Atlantic 10). Darnell Harris had 19 points, and Rodney Green 12 for La Salle (6-8, 0-2), which dropped its fifth straight. UMass trailed by 14 points midway through the first half, and 37-33 at halftime. But the Minutemen went on a 13-4 run at the start of the second half and moved out to a 45-41 lead. A three-point play by Gary Forbes gave UMass a 66-57 edge with 4:55 to play, but the Explores rallied within 71-67 at the 1:05 mark. The Minutemen then made 10 straight free throws down the stretch to seal the victory. Lasme, third in the nation in blocked shots, has 74 for the season.
